<POST>
<POSTER> jim beam &lt;spamvor...@bad.example.net&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-03-03T08:40:00 </POSTDATE>
<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
mfivespeed wrote:
&gt; how do you adjust the parking break on a honda crx?
">

the cable adjuster is under the center console, behind the parking brake
lever.  the rear calipers or drums are supposed to be self adjusting.
if they're not, you may need to strip and clean them - that doesn't
require cable adjustment.

but why do you need to adjust?  unless you've changed the cables or have
badly fitting after-market brake shoes, you should never need to touch it.
</POST>
